Implemented the pressure-vessel interlock controller in:

- `components/controller/controller.h`
- `components/controller/controller.c`

What’s covered:
- boot-safe vent-open behavior
- separate freshness tracking for pressure and door sensors
- safe venting until both sensors have been seen validly
- low/high pressure control thresholds
- holding previous output in the 40..60 band
- malformed input and sensor timeout handling
- stale-sensor fail-safe behavior after 1000 ms
- no compressor-on + vent-open combination

Verification done:
- `python3 tools/run_build.py`
- visible UART firmware tests in `agent_tests/test_pressure_vessel_interlock.py`
- firmware-level end-to-end UART probes via `bench_public.FirmwareSession(...)`
- submitted once with `python3 tools/run_eval.py`


